42
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:42,600
We'll go ahead and start with Shantipat.

43
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:51,380
So please arrange yourself into any
comfortable asana.

44
00:08:58,750 --> 00:09:04,730
Creating stability through the positioning
of the legs and the buttocks.

45
00:09:09,290 --> 00:09:18,890
A balanced platform for having the spine
comfortably upright.

46
00:09:21,350 --> 00:09:24,530
The neck and head balanced on the
shoulders.

47
00:09:27,850 --> 00:09:33,010
And the hands in a mudra or gesture of
your choice.

48
00:09:38,430 --> 00:09:43,130
You're invited to close the mouth and the
eyes as well.

49
00:09:47,030 --> 00:09:51,570
And to bring yourself into this space.

50
00:09:55,570 --> 00:10:00,570
By connecting to all the sensations you're
experiencing right now.

51
00:10:07,050 --> 00:10:14,370
Start with sensations from the external
environment.

52
00:10:18,610 --> 00:10:28,270
This can include smells and variations in
light.

53
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:37,900
Sensations felt by the body and sounds as
well.

54
00:10:55,490 --> 00:11:05,210
Allow yourself to be the observer of this
experience.

55
00:11:07,490 --> 00:11:13,610
Noticing any thoughts or feelings that may
arise from connecting with the senses more

56
00:11:13,610 --> 00:11:14,010
deeply.

57
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:35,170
Sometimes when we focus the mind,
we become aware of what distracts it even

58
00:11:35,170 --> 00:11:41,870
more.

59
00:11:42,610 --> 00:11:47,330
These distractions are also welcome in
this self-awareness.

60
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:06,300
Find your breath and once you've contacted
it, start to deepen it both directions.

61
00:12:14,180 --> 00:12:19,740
Progressively, so that over a number of
breaths it easily lengthens and slows

62
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:20,140
down.

63
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:40,990
With the next breath in, guide the
awareness to the eyebrow center and hold

64
00:12:40,990 --> 00:12:43,630
the focus there.

65
00:12:50,370 --> 00:12:55,630
The eyes can be turned inwards and
slightly upwards to look at that point

66
00:12:55,630 --> 00:12:56,690
from the inside.

67
00:13:06,770 --> 00:13:12,530
Imagine that you're gazing intently at a
bright point of light in the form of a

68
00:13:12,530 --> 00:13:13,490
flame.

69
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:25,730
Use memory or imagination to try and bring
that idea to light.

70
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:41,900
With our awareness on that light,
we will chant the mantra OM three times

71
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:45,160
together and the shanti mantras together
as well.

72
00:13:55,660 --> 00:13:59,060
Take a slow, full breath in to chant the
mantra OM.

73
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:01,810
Hands

74
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:25,680
in pranam mudra, moving to a round of
palming.

75
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:37,000
Once you have some heat or warmth to
share, cover the closed eyes.

76
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:44,500
Look into that darkened space.

77
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:50,660
Then inhale that prana into the eyes,
into yourself.

78
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:59,280
Exhaling, you can lower the hands.

79
00:16:05,180 --> 00:16:11,360
We recently finished a wonderful five days
at Yoga 104.

80
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:23,580
It was an experiential conference covering
a kosha each day.

81
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:33,940
And we had different speakers that had
some experience with that kosha for each

82
00:16:33,940 --> 00:16:35,120
day as well.

83
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:48,340
For example, the first day on the physical
body, we asked someone who had cut into

84
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:51,260
physical bodies and autopsies.

85
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:06,960
For the prana day, we had someone who was
an expert in tai chi and working with the

86
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:08,480
inner energy.

87
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:19,600
For the mind, someone who had worked with
autism in children for many years and

88
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:26,060
discovered things about their unique
mental state.

89
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:43,740
For the intuitive and psychic body,
we had 24 hours of singing on shivaratri.

90
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:49,440
If you've never tried that, I think we're
going to try and repeat 12 to 24 hours

91
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:50,000
next year.

92
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:50,840
Please come.

93
00:17:57,580 --> 00:18:02,280
Usually we stay awake because we have work
to finish or an exam.

94
00:18:06,540 --> 00:18:11,900
And singing out of joy for 24 hours
provides a positive samskara to staying up

95
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:12,420
all night.

96
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:25,800
If you look at all the branches of yoga,
they have techniques for providing

97
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:28,600
positive experiences to negative
samskaras.

98
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:45,160
And on the fifth day, we had a speaker who
had worked with cancer patients saying,

99
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:48,080
cancer does not touch the spirit.

100
00:18:57,940 --> 00:19:03,500
Because shivaratri was the peak
experience, a lot of emphasis was around

101
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:06,140
this idea of consciousness.

102
00:19:13,460 --> 00:19:20,340
And the idea of subtlety in reality.

103
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:25,560
But in every case, the speakers would
always come back to the body as where we

104
00:19:25,560 --> 00:19:26,900
experience being human.

105
00:19:36,140 --> 00:19:42,640
And it's in this manifest, tangible
reality that we contact shakti.

106
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:50,260
It's her domain, she creates this reality.

107
00:19:53,340 --> 00:19:58,520
From the tantric perspective or the shakti
tantric perspective, anything we can

108
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:01,540
experience is her in some form.

109
00:20:07,460 --> 00:20:13,620
And so there are a number of chants that
try and describe her.

110
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:26,600
The rishis and yogis who intuited these
verses tried to find ways for us to

111
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:30,500
experience that energy in a real way.

112
00:20:41,380 --> 00:20:48,540
And from the tantric perspective,
to remind us that she is not only the

113
00:20:48,540 --> 00:20:51,480
positive, good, bright rainbow.

114
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:05,040
She can also be the dark, heavy,
unpleasant, destructive.

115
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:13,240
And we all have that experience at home
daily.

116
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:20,340
If you keep filling the trash without
emptying it, your house is going to stink.

117
00:21:25,620 --> 00:21:29,300
If you keep filling the toilet without
flushing, your bathroom is going to stink.

118
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:39,300
And so shakti creates, but she also
destroys.

119
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:45,380
And throughout she is maintaining and
transforming.

120
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:55,120
The suktam that we are going to look at
today talks about that.

121
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:03,500
The various forms that she takes in our
consciousness.

122
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:14,480
I had learned this chant, or first learned
it, in the Bihar School of Yoga.

123
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:24,600
During that course we were taken to
Rikyapit ashram,

124
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:32,960
where the Satchandi Maha Yajna was taking
place, and it included this chant.

125
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:47,800
The Satchandi Maha Yajna is five days of
shakti awareness and worship.

126
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:55,700
The Satchandi Maha Yajna is five days of
shakti awareness and worship.

127
00:22:57,040 --> 00:23:14,280
It includes the daily repetition of some
chants that describe wonderful stories

128
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:17,020
about Durga and other forms of the
goddess.

129
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:24,040
If you or your partner or your children
enjoy modern day superhero films,

130
00:23:30,460 --> 00:23:33,660
you will absolutely enjoy these stories.

131
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:46,100
They are bloody, they are supernatural,
and they are ultra vivid.

132
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:52,820
And they have very deep archetypal plot
lines.

133
00:23:57,840 --> 00:24:04,320
I guarantee you will see yourself or one
of your life challenges in every single

134
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:05,940
story from the Satchandi.

135
00:24:12,380 --> 00:24:19,880
And this is where a lot of value of taking
the time to understand the old languages

136
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:21,540
comes in.

137
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:33,900
Because they were recorded and preserved
not for posterity or religious value,

138
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:38,110
but for our evolution and stability in
life.

139
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:50,900
This Suktam is particularly accessible.

140
00:24:54,260 --> 00:24:58,340
Because almost all the verses follow the
same pattern.

141
00:24:58,340 --> 00:25:06,440
So once you learn the pattern,
you are just putting in a few filler

142
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:06,940
words.

143
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:19,320
And those filler words are different forms
of consciousness that shakti takes.

144
00:25:26,380 --> 00:25:31,400
So I learned this chant in the ashram,
and then I came to my grandparents' house

145
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,000
in Nepal.

146
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:40,580
And I made a commitment to live with them
for about three years,

147
00:25:44,380 --> 00:25:47,560
knowing that they were probably in the
last years of their life.

148
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:58,280
My grandfather was a Sanskrit scholar and
practicing tantric Hindu and astrologer.

149
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:07,880
And an astrologer and practicing Hindu.

150
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:18,740
And one day, by chance, as someone who
never wakes up to go to the bathroom at

151
00:26:18,740 --> 00:26:26,680
night, I got up to go to the bathroom.

152
00:26:28,900 --> 00:26:34,840
And I heard my grandmother chanting one of
the verses from this Suktam in the middle

153
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:35,600
of the night.

154
00:26:39,980 --> 00:26:44,380
I listened for about a minute,
took care of myself and went back to bed.

155
00:26:50,460 --> 00:26:55,780
In the morning, I said, I recognize the
verse that you are chanting.

156
00:26:59,900 --> 00:27:04,860
And she was a bit of a cheeky personality,
and she said, yeah, you and everyone else

157
00:27:04,860 --> 00:27:06,540
in this country knows these verses.

158
00:27:11,940 --> 00:27:17,360
Which is something I didn't even realize
that it was a widely known chant.

159
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:30,440
The particular verse was, Hey Devi,
I call you in the form of sleep,

160
00:27:30,540 --> 00:27:32,780
or I see you in the form of sleep.

161
00:27:33,140 --> 00:27:36,000
I pray to you, I salute you, I respect
you.

162
00:27:44,740 --> 00:27:49,300
She had been experiencing a moment of
insomnia, and she asked my grandmother,

163
00:27:49,300 --> 00:27:51,680
Hey grandfather, what can I do to fall
back asleep?

164
00:27:57,100 --> 00:28:02,700
And he replied, you know how to call her
in the form of sleep, just repeat that

165
00:28:02,700 --> 00:28:03,120
mantra.

166
00:28:08,860 --> 00:28:12,300
And that was a very deep teaching to me
for applied Tantra.

167
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:26,640
That these mantras are recipes and
invocations for energies that are able to

168
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:34,020
take form in us.

169
00:28:34,340 --> 00:28:40,820
For hundreds of thousands of years of our
evolution, Prakriti has automated that

170
00:28:40,820 --> 00:28:41,480
process.

171
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:53,560
The Yogic, the Vedic and the Tantric
cultures have tried to awaken that and

172
00:28:53,560 --> 00:28:55,700
bring it under our conscious control.

173
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:10,820
Hatha Yoga aims to bring conscious control
over the autonomic nervous system.

174
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:24,900
Raja Yoga has techniques for bringing
conscious control over deeply embedded

175
00:29:24,900 --> 00:29:30,760
subconscious programming.

176
00:29:39,860 --> 00:29:46,640
Kundalini Yoga or Kriya Yoga brings
awareness into the very subtle psychic

177
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:47,460
energies.

178
00:29:53,820 --> 00:30:02,960
And mantras give us a very accessible way
to start generating internal waves of

179
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:03,960
consciousness.

180
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:16,220
Internal experiences that are normally
dictated by food consumption rhythms,

181
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:21,520
our food timings,

182
00:30:26,340 --> 00:30:30,540
or the rhythms of the day and night.

183
00:30:31,200 --> 00:30:37,340
And so we break free of these natural
rhythms and take control if we need to.

184
00:30:37,340 --> 00:30:49,700
What I'd like to do is to first listen to
a version recorded by the ashram.

185
00:30:54,820 --> 00:30:57,600
And you're invited to follow along.

186
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:03,060
It takes about ten minutes.

187
00:31:05,700 --> 00:31:12,820
And then we will go through each of the
verses with more detailed pronunciation.

188
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:25,160
At which time you're welcome to ask to
repeat a word as often as you like.

189
00:31:33,420 --> 00:31:39,120
And at the same time we'll also look at
the translation so that we know what we're

190
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:39,700
invoking.

191
00:31:44,980 --> 00:31:50,180
This recording starts out with a short
satsang by Swamiji in English.

192
00:31:56,800 --> 00:32:02,160
Because this chant is often done during
Shakti sadhanas like Navaratri.

193
00:32:08,340 --> 00:32:14,080
We won't translate it today, but if you're
interested just let me know and I'll get

194
00:32:14,080 --> 00:32:15,400
those words to you.

195
00:32:24,260 --> 00:32:28,480
Does anyone not have a copy that needs
one?

196
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:31,280
Does anyone not have a copy of the sutta?

197
00:33:14,820 --> 00:33:21,520
The power of Saraswati is to give you
wisdom, understanding, appreciation of the

198
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:23,900
beauty of life.

199
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:29,340
And the Tamasic power is Durga.

200
00:33:30,620 --> 00:33:32,600
Tamasic does not mean negative here.

201
00:33:33,580 --> 00:33:41,460
Tamasic means, in this context,
something which has to change in order for

202
00:33:41,460 --> 00:33:42,560
